CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 16, 1951, pg. 18, reads: "Homewood Pianist Gives Recital - Talented and charming Miss Irene Wright, 23, 7345 Idlewild Street, was presented in a senior recital at the Pittsburgh Musical Institute last Friday evening. Miss Wright, a student of the institute for four years, was awarded her diploma at the conclusion of the recital. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Irene Wright performing piano recital at Pittsburgh Musical Institute
